A vast ocean viewed from above, with a small wooden sailboat navigating through swirling, concentric ripples that spiral outward in mesmerizing patterns. The water shifts between deep navy and turquoise, creating natural zoom-like layers that draw the eye from the distant horizon down to intricate wave details. Scattered across the water's surface are floating geometric shapes—circles, squares, triangles—arranged in deliberate pathways like stepping stones. The scene captures both the exhilarating freedom of fluid movement and the subtle danger of disorientation. Dramatic storm clouds gather on one edge while golden sunlight breaks through on the other, suggesting the fine line between captivating motion and overwhelming chaos. Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, dreamy atmospheric lighting, and that signature sense of wonder mixed with slight unease.
